wpt.desc: A Cache for Wendy's Picnic by MikeOtt, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: A Cache for Wendy's Picnic
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
This cache is located in the Carpenter Area of White Clay Creek State Park, that is reached from Rt 896. From May to October this is a fee area. (Better yet get an annual pass to Delaware State parks)

It was released at the same time as the Dog Days of Summer Picnic geocaching event in the park hosted by WhiteClayLover that I have called "Wendy's Picnic".

The cache is a camo medium tupperware cantainer located in the Fitness trail section of the park that is generally sticker free. Ther are many trails to the cache (none direct) so look at the park map. At one time there was a cache in this general area.

The cache contains an unactivated travel bug tag provided by WhiteClayLover as a FTF
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:encoded_hints: Base of big beech tree near oak and double beech tree

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Didn't get good GPS readings, so we used the hint.
